11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 804, as
13 amended by Section 28, Chapter 310, O.S.L. 2023 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
14 Section 804), is amended to read as follows:
15 Section 804. A. No person shall act as an instructor unless
16 such person applies for and obtains from Service Oklahoma a license
17 in the manner and form prescribed by Service Oklahoma.
18 B. Rules promulgated by Service Oklahoma, in conjunction with
19 the Department of Public Safety, shall state the requirements for an
20 instructor’s license, including requirements concerning moral
21 character, physical condition, knowledge of the courses of
22 instruction, motor vehicle laws and safety principles and practices,
23 previous personnel and employment records, and such other matters as
